ernational helicopter community<ref>[http://helicopterannual.org/portals/27/pdf/ann_p6c4.pdf \u201cSalute to Excellence\u201d Awards] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006220054/http://helicopterannual.org/portals/27/pdf/ann_p6c4.pdf |date=2013-10-06 }}, 2009 Helicopter Annual</ref><ref>{{cite journal|magazine=AOPA Pilot|title=HAI Announces Winners of Salute to Excellence Awards|date=March 2015|page=26}}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Segrave Trophy]] || [[Royal Automobile Club]] || Outstanding Skill, Courage and Initiative on Land, Water and in the Airfirst person to hold both the land and water speed records simultaneously.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-35758176 | title = Sir Henry Segrave: The legacy of the 200 mph record breaker| first = Helen |last = Carter| publisher= BBC News | accessdate = 2 December 2017 | date = 16 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.royalautomobileclub.co.uk/motoring/trophies/the-segrave-trophy/history/| title = The Segrave Trophy \u2013 history | publisher = Royal Automobile Club| accessdate = 13 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Americas || [[SICOFAA Legion of Merit Medal]] || [[System of Cooperation Among the American Air Forces]] || Military members or civilians who have contributed to and promoted the interests of SICOFAA<ref>[http://sicofaa.org/files/archivos/documentos_normativos/Estatuto_Legion_Merito_Mayo_2009.pdf Information on the history, protocol and description of the award]</ref>\n|-\n| United States and Canada || [[Superior Airmanship Award]] || [[Air Line Pilots Association, International ]] || Superior airmanship (safety)<ref>[http://www.alpa.org/alpa/DesktopModules/ViewDocument.aspx?DocumentID=932 ALPA Annual Air Safety Awards Banquet] - ALPA honors its members who advance aviation safety while flying the line or in volunteer work on their days off.</ref><ref>[http://www.alpa.org/Default.aspx?tabid=483 Crewroom > ASF 2005] - ALPA Honors Award Recipients at Air Safety Forum</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Tony Jannus Award]] || Tony Jannus Distinguished Aviation Society || Individual achievement in scheduled commercial aviation by airline executives, inventors and manufacturers, and government leaders<ref>{{cite news|title=Rickenbacker is honored for assistance to airlines|date=January 21, 1967|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1967/01/21/82993793.pdf|accessdate=2009-01-27 | format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tony Jannus, an enduring legacy of aviation |work=Tony Jannus Distinguished Aviation Society |url=http://www.tonyjannusaward.com/history.html |accessdate=October 27, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070716153330/http://tonyjannusaward.com/history.html |archivedate=July 16, 2007 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[William J. Kossler Award]] || [[Vertical Flight Society]] || Greatest achievement in practical application or operation of rotary wing aircraft<ref>[http://vtol.org/customIncludes/showAwards.cfm?awardID=8 \"Captain William J. Kossler, USCG Award\"]. Accessed 31 May 2013.</ref> \n|-\n| United States || [[Wright Brothers Medal]] || [[SAE International]] || Notable contributions in the engineering, design, development, or operation of air and space vehicles<ref>{{cite book|title=Significant American and international awards in aviation|author=United States. Navy Dept. Bureau of Aeronautics|year=1954|pages=91\u201392|url=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?seq=11&view=image&size=100&id=mdp.39015018432529&u=1&num=91|publisher=Washington}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Awards, Honors, and Prizes|author=Wasserman, P.|year=1975|page=363|volume=1|publisher=Gale Company|url=https://books.google.com/?id=AnhMAAAAYAAJ&dq=%22wright%20brothers%20medal%22%20-langley|isbn=9780810303768}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Bulletin of the National Research Council|author=National Academy of Sciences|year=1934|page=116|url=https://books.google.com