cinghistory.freeola.com/Between%20the%20wars(2).htm \"The Bendix Trophy\"], ''Air Racing History'', retrieved January 6, 2006</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060211160117/http://www.aeromuseum.org/Articles/July04/QuestForSpeed.htm \"The Quest for Speed Bendix Air Races 1931 to 1949\"] From Air Trails, September 1950</ref>\n|-\n| France || [[Coupe Deutsch de la Meurthe]] || [[A\u00e9ro-Club de France]] || Speed trial for powered aircraft over a distance of 200 kilometres, to be flown as an outward leg of 100 km followed by a return to the starting point<ref>[http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k6551284g/f7.image.r=Deutsch%20de%20la%20Meurthe Bulletin Officiel de l'A\u0117ro-Club de France] [[l'A\u0117rophile]], March 1906, p.71</ref><ref>{{cite |journal=Flight |url=https://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1919/1919%20-%201366.html |title=Coupe Henry Deutsch de l a Meurthe |volume=XI |number=564|date=16 October 1919 |page= 1368}}</ref>\n|-\n| United Kingdom || [[Daily Mail aviation prizes]] || ''[[Daily Mail]]'' newspaper || Various competitions<ref>[http://www.flightglobal.com/PDFArchive/View/1913/1913%20-%200958.html \"Direct initiative of Lord Northcliffe] Flight\" PDF Archive, 6 September 1913</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Such |first1=Colin |title=The Daily Mail's Sponsorship of British Pioneer Aviation |url=https://www.warwickandwarwick.com/resources/articles-library/the-daily-mails-sponsorship-of-british-pioneer-aviation |website=Warwick & Warwick |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| International || [[De la Vaulx Medal]] || [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration A\u00e9ronautique Internationale]] || Holders of recognized absolute world aviation records<ref>{{citation |accessdate=2020-02-14 |url=https://www.fai.org/awards |title=FAI Awards : The De La Vaulx Medal |publisher=FAI }}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Dole Air Race]] || [[James Dole]] || Air race across the Pacific Ocean from northern [[California]] to the [[Territory of Hawaii]]<ref>{{cite web|titl