020-02-15 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060621111910/http://www.airforce.forces.gc.ca/abroaddocs/abroad_3_2_e.asp |title=International Competitions |publisher=Air Force Public Affairs / Department of National Defence (Canada)}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Octave Chanute Award]] || [[American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics]] || Pilot(s) or test personnel that contributed to the advancement of the art, science, or technology of aeronautics<ref>{{cite web |title=Chanute Flight Test Award Recipients |url=https://www.aiaa.org/get-involved/honors-awards/awards/award/award-chanute-flight-test-award |website=AIAA |publisher=American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics |accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Onizuka Prop Wash Award]] || [[U.S. Air Force Test Pilot School]] || Student at the USAF TPS who contributed most to class spirit and morale<ref>{{cite web |last= Taylor |first=Annamaria |title = TPS class 09A graduates |url= http://www.edwards.af.mil/News/Article/395451/tps-class-09a-graduates/ |publisher=United States Air Force |date=January 6, 2010 |accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title = USAF Test Pilot School 50 Years and Beyond |publisher=Privately Published |year=1994 |page = 220}}</ref>\n|-\n| Australia || [[Oswald Watt Gold Medal]] || Royal Federation of Aero Clubs of Australia || A most brilliant performance in the air or the most notable contribution to aviation by an Australian or in Australia<ref>{{cite web|url = http://rfaca.com.au/awards/| title= Awards|publisher= Royal Federation of Aero Clubs of Australia|accessdate = 31 August 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| United States || [[Pilot Proficiency Award Program]] || [[Federal Aviation Administration]] || General aviation pilots knowledge and proficiency (safety)<ref>*[https://web.archive.org/web/20161222234937/https://www.faasafety.gov/about/ac61-91h.pdf FAA Advisory Circular 61-91H: Pilot Proficiency Award Program (PDF)]</ref>\n|-\n| International || 