= ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n|rev4score = 7.4/10<ref name=\"PF\">{{cite web|url=http://pitchforkmedia.com/reviews/albums/4585-joyful-rebellion|title=k-os: Joyful Rebellion|last=Miller|first=Derek|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=October 5, 2004|accessdate=November 30, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''RapReviews''\n|rev5score = 8.5/10<ref name=\"RR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rapreviews.com/archive/2004_09F_joyful.html|title=Feature for September 28, 2004 - k-os' \"Joyful Rebellion\"|last=Mennella|first=Dan|website=RapReviews|date=September 28, 2004|accessdate=August 6, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n|rev6score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/kos/albums/album/6292093/review/6583078/joyful_rebellion|title=K-OS: Joyful Rebellion|last=Hoard|first=Christian|authorlink=Christian Hoard|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]]|date=October 5, 2004|accessdate=August 6, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090303095204/https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/kos/albums/album/6292093/review/6583078/joyful_rebellion|archivedate=March 3, 2009}}</ref>\n|rev7 = [[Sputnikmusic]]\n|rev7score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"Sputnik\">{{cite web|url=http://sputnikmusic.com/album.php?albumid=4180|title=k-os - Joyful Rebellion|author=FlawedPerfection|website=[[Sputnikmusic]]|date=January 31, 2007|accessdate=August 6, 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Joyful Rebellion''''' is the second album of [[alternative hip hop]] artist [[k-os]]. It was released 13 August 2004 in [[Canada]] by [[EMI]] and 21 September 2004 in the [[United States]] by [[Virgin Records]]. It debuted at number 7 on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]], and went platinum in Canada, selling over 100,000 units.\n\n==Awards==\n*The [[Much (TV channel)|MuchMusic]] Video Awards (MMVA's)\n**2005 Best Pop Video (\"Crabbuckit\")\n**2005 MuchVibe Best Rap Video (\"Man I Used To Be\")\n*[[Juno Awards]]\n**2005 Single of the Year (\"Crabbuckit\")\n**2005 Rap Recording of the Year (\"Joyful Rebellion\")\n**2005 Video of the Year (\"B-Boy Stance\")\n*Canadian Urban Music Awards\n**2004 Hip Hop Recording of the Year (\"B-Boy Stance\")\n**2004 Music Video of the Year (\"B-Boy Stance\")\n\nAt the [[2017 Polaris Music Prize]], the album won the jury vote for the Heritage Prize in the 1996-2005 category.<ref name=heritage>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/music/2017/10/24/tragically-hip-album-makes-polaris-heritage-prize-list.html|title=Tragically Hip album makes Polaris Heritage Prize list|last=Rayner|first=Ben|newspaper=[[Toronto Star]]|publisher=Toronto Star Newspapers Ltd.|date=October 24, 2017|accessdate=October 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Lyrics==\nLike ''[[Exit (k-os album)|Exit]]'', ''Joyful Rebellion'' primarily focuses on [[k-os]]'s negative views of the music industry, supplemented by more metaphorical lyrics.\n\nThe track \"[[Man I Used to Be]]\" is about a man who wants to revert to his previous self. The tracks \"[[The Love Song (k-os song)|The Love Song]]\" and \"The Mirror\" are semi-autobiographical. The song \"One Blood\" is an anti-war message. The song \"Papercutz\" is k-os's denial that ''Exit'' was his last album. \"Commandante\" features the opening sample of a woman speaking in Spanish on a voice mail.\n\n==Track listing==\n# \"EMCEE Murdah\" \u2013 3:30\n# \"Crucial\" \u2013 3:25\n# \"[[Man I Used to Be]]\" \u2013 5:04\n# \"[[Crabbuckit]]\" \u2013 3:48\n# \"B-Boy Stance\" \u2013 4:00\n# \"Commandante\" \u2013 3:45\n# \"[[The Love Song (k-os song)|The Love Song]]\" \u2013 4:18\n# \"Hallelujah\" \u2013 4:17\n# \"Clap Ur Handz\" \u2013 1:20\n# \"Neutroniks\" - 3:51\n# \"Dirty Water\" (featuring [[Sam Roberts]]) \u2013 4:14\n# \"One Blood (Jiggy Homicide)\" \u2013 3:29\n# \"Papercutz\" (featuring [[Kamau]]) \u2013 15:27\n#* \"The Mirror\" (Hidden track)\n\nNOTE: \"Neutroniks\" is only featured on the Canadian version of the album. The song appears on all versions (except the Canadian edition) of his previous album ''[[Exit (k-os album)|Exit]]''.\n\n==Singles==\n*\"[[Crabbuckit]]\"\n*\"B-Boy Stance\"\n*\"[[Man I Used to Be]]\"\n*\"The Love Song\"\n*\"Crucial\"\n*\"Dirty Water\"\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2004)\n!align=\"center\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Canadian Albums Chart]]<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/esearch/searchResult.jsp?configType=BBCOM_SIMPLEDEFAULT&pubList=Billboard&an=bbcom&action=Submit&kw=&exposeNavigation=true&keyword=k-os+Joyful+Rebellion+top+canadian+albums&searchType=ARTICLE_SEARCH Top Canadian Albums Chart Listings], billboard.com</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|- \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{K-os}}\n\n[[Category:2004 albums]]\n[[Category:K-os albums]]\n[[Category:EMI Records albums]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Hipposonic Studios]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded at Metalworks Studios]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Rap Recording of the Year recordings]]\n\n{{2004-hiphop-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Joyful Rebellion\n| type       = [[Album]]\n| artist     = [[k-os]]\n| cover      = Joyfulrebel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 13 August 2004 (Canada)<br>2006 (United States)\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = {{collapsible list|title={{nobold|Various}}|ubl=true|Umbrella Sound <small>(Toronto)</small>|[[The Warehouse Studio]] <small>(Vancouver)</small>|Reaction Studios <small>(Toronto)</small>|306 Studios <small>(Toronto)</small>|[[Hipposonic Studios]] <small>(Vancouver)</small>|[[Metalworks Studios]] <small>(Mississauga)</small>|Blacksmith Studios <small>(Toronto)</small>}}\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Hip hop music|Rap]]|[[alternative hip hop]]}}\n| length     = {{Duration|m=57|s=59}}\n| label      = [[Virgin Records]] (U.S.)<br />[[EMI]] (Canada)\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n*[[k-os]]\n*[[Greg O'Shea]]\n*[[Kevon Edmonds]]\n*[[Babyface (musician)|Kenny \"Babyface\" Edmonds]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Exit (k-os album)|Exit]]\n| prev_year  = 2002\n| next_title = [[Atlantis: Hymns for Disco]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|url={{AllMusic|class=album|id=r707136|pure_url=yes}}|title=Joyful Rebellion - k-os|last=Loftus|first=Johnny|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=August 6, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[HipHopDX]]''\n|rev2score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"HHDX\">{{cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/reviews/id.471/title.k-os-joyful-rebellion|title=k-os - Joyful Rebellion|author=J-23|website=[[HipHopDX]]|publisher=Cheri Media Group|date=September 21, 2004|accessdate=January 5, 2020}}</ref>\n|rev3 = Obnoxious Listeners\n|rev3score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>[http://www.obnoxiouslisteners.com/album/joyful-rebellion-k-os/ Obnoxious Listeners review] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114075415/http://www.obnoxiouslisteners.com/album/joyful-rebellion-k-os/ |date=2009-01-14 }}</ref>\n|rev4 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n|rev4score = 7.4/10<ref name=\"PF\">{{cite web|url=http://pitchforkmedia.com/reviews/albums/4585-joyful-rebellion|title=k-os: Joyful Rebellion|last=Miller|first=Derek|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=October 5, 2004|accessdate=November 30, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''RapReviews''\n|rev5score = 8.5/10<ref name=\"RR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rapreviews.com/archive/2004_09F_joyful.html|title=Feature for September 28, 2004 - k-os' \"Joyful Rebellion\"|last=Mennella|first=Dan|website=RapReviews|date=September 28, 2004|accessdate=August 6, 2011}}</ref>\n|rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n|rev6score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/artists/kos/albums/album/6292093/review/6583078/joyful_rebellion|title=K-OS: Joyful Rebellion|last=Hoard|first=Christian|authorlink=Christian Hoard|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]]|date